# oauth2-proxy allow-list (Q10.5) — EXAMPLE. One Google account e-mail per line.
#
# The real file `authenticated-emails.txt` is gitignored (it lists real accounts).
# The first-boot flow materializes it from OAUTH2_PROXY_ALLOWED_EMAILS in .env:
# each comma/space-separated entry becomes one line here. You may also edit it by
# hand and `docker compose restart oauth2-proxy`.
#
# Placeholders only — replace with the accounts you actually permit:
you@gmail.com
other-allowed@gmail.com
